{
  "texts": [
    "Across the publications that reported any preprocessing, we found that there were seven main preprocessing groups: Artifact Removal, Data Scaling, Data Augmentation, Coordinate Transformation, Windowing, Image Processing, and Fixation Filtering.",
    "Artifact Removal involves removing any unwanted data points, such as blinks, noise, or outliers.",
    "Most publications reported using the eye tracking manufacturer's software for blink detection and removal.",
    "However, it was different for other artifacts.",
    "For example, Alghofaili et al. (2019) used a Moving Average filter, and George and Routray (2016) used a Savitzky-Golay filter to remove noise, while Lan et al."
  ]
}